Preface: - Mouje Nivli Ravanangwadi, Ta. Technical approval to the original budget has been granted by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Ratnagiri, vide order No. (2) in respect of the budget of the Correctional Re-connection Tap Water Supply Scheme at Ratnagiri, ZP. Also, the original administrative approval for the scheme has been granted under the order at No. (1) in the context. Accordingly, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Ratnagiri has submitted a proposal to the Government under letter no. (3) under reference for grant of revised administrative approval to the existing tap water supply scheme on account of increase in the cost of the scheme on account of overcharging tender. The Government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price subject to the revised technical approval granted by the competent authorities under the order in reference No. (4).
The Government's Decisions:

Mouje Nivli Ravanangwadi, Ta., under Jal Jeevan PRA Programme. vide order No. (1) in respect of the Correctional Re-linking Scheme at Ratnagiri, Z. Ratnagiri, Rs. 1,50,58, 257 / - for a nominal price has been given administrative approval under Jal Jeevan PRM programme. Excessive bid costs have led to an increase in the price of the scheme.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2024 / P.No.116 / Papu-04

The plan of Rs. The revised administrative approval is being granted subject to the following conditions for a nominal price of 1,71,66, 413 / - (Rupees One Crore Seventy One Lakh Sixty Six Thousand Four Hundred and Thirteen Only).
Conditions
The Chief Executive Officer / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

Once the scheme is completed, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of STATA notification that the scheme has been actually completed by the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad.

Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and if any defects are found in the SAT inspection, they should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred annually for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
On completion of the scheme, it is mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad) to transfer the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

According to a CAG report in 2013, 21% of the water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to lack of maintenance and non-payment of electricity charges. In this case, the Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for increasing the water tariff as per the requirement in order to make the scheme financially viable.
7. Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on corruption.
8. The District Council shall be responsible for ensuring that the present scheme is not revised under any circumstances.
9. Since administrative expenditure is not admissible under Jal Jeevan FR, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
